title: $:/plugins/rimir/kind/changelog
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|v0.1.57 |2026-06-02 |''New: ''Kind: Instances Overview'' graph view.'' A whole-wiki graph of every kind instance (`[all[tiddlers]has[kind.type]!has[kind.fields]]`), shipped as the openable tiddler ''Kind: Instances Overview'' + a default config shadow. Built entirely on existing `kind.*` engine functions + the flibbles/graph widget toolkit (soft-dep — shows an install hint when no graph engine is present). ''Features:'' nodes coloured per type (12-colour palette indexed by sorted type position, or an optional per-type `kind.color` field override); deterministic grid seed positions so the layout never reshuffles on reload/filter, with user drags persisted to `$:/config/rimir/kind/instances-overview/structure` (override wins over the seed); a search box (`search:caption,title`); an ''Edges'' checkbox row generated from the union of all ref-typed field keys across all kinds (`listField` selection, ships defaulting to `parent`); a colour-coded ''Types'' row that shows/hides instances per type via a //hidden-types// list (default empty = all shown) using a negation-free count/`compare:integer` toggle; double-click a node to open it; hover for an icon+type+caption tooltip. ''Implementation note:'' the whole view is deliberately negation-free — `get[field]` returns nothing for missing/empty fields so `~` fallbacks replace `!is[blank]`, and ref-field discovery filters on the positive `kind.is-ref-typed` predicate. ''Touches:'' new `instances-overview.tid`, new `config-instances-overview-edge-fields.tid`; docs (readme, doc/overview, doc/reference). ''Restart required'' (new plugin tiddlers). |
|v0.1.56 |2026-06-01 |''Fix: dependent-default cascade didn't re-fire on ref/enum pick in either creator OR cascade-palette.'' User report after 0.1.55: //"neither creator nor cp does fill caption when selecting a jour-fixe"//. Three coupled bugs in 0.1.55. ''(1) Render-time gating in `kind.apply-defaults-to`.'' v0.1.55 used a nested `<$list>` with `filter="[function[kind.compute-default]…!is[blank]] :filter[!has<field-key>]"` to decide whether to render a setfield for each field. TW's `<$list>` evaluates its filter at RENDER time and its children become part of the action chain — but the trailer was transcluded inside the ref-pick `<$button>`, so the procedure body was rendered when the button itself was rendered (before any click). At that point, parent was blank, so compute-default for caption returned empty, the gate excluded caption, and caption's setfield was never even in the action chain to fire after the ref-pick committed parent. ''Fix:'' move the gate INTO the setfield's `$value` (via three-tier `{{{filter}}}` — existing-non-blank → compute-default-if-non-blank → existing-fallback). `{{{filter}}}` IS evaluated at action-fire time, so each setfield sees the just-set dependency. The outer-list gate is now "does this field have a `default` property?" (static — depends only on schema) so it correctly skips fields without defaults at render time (avoiding empty-field bloat). Same fix applied to `kind.force-apply-defaults`. ''(2) CP ref-pick / enum-pick had no trailer at all.'' The CP path's drill-row candidates (`kind.ref-leaf-build` for single-ref, `kind.enum-leaf-one` for single-enum) only fired `<$action-setfield>` for the binding — no `kind.apply-defaults-to` follow-up. Different code path from `field-input.tid` (which I'd patched in 0.1.55) so CP create flow had no re-fire at all. ''Fix:'' threaded `type-tid` through `kind.ref-leaf-items` → `kind.ref-leaf-one` → `kind.ref-leaf-build` (and `kind.enum-leaf-items` → `kind.enum-leaf-one`); each `ca-actions` now trails `<$transclude $variable="kind.apply-defaults-to" type-tid=… target-tid=…/>` after the setfield. Multi-card (`kind.ref-toggle-*`, `kind.enum-toggle-*`) uses `ca-kind:"toggle"` with `ca-bind-*` instead of `ca-actions`, so the binding is CP-engine-internal and there's no hook for a trailer — deferred to a future CP feature. ''(3) Caption formula used `HH:mm` which renders literally as "HH:30".'' TW datetime format codes are case-sensitive: `HH` doesn't exist (cf. [[tw-gotchas-540-migration]]). Fixed to `0DD.0MM.YYYY 0hh:0mm` everywhere (caption default in `conversation.tid`, doc/reference example). User said //"1on1 with Lisa at 25.06.2026 15:00"// so padded date + 24h padded hours matches their format expectation. ''Touches:'' `engine.tid` (`kind.apply-defaults-to` + `kind.force-apply-defaults` restructured — gate-in-$value pattern), `cascade-helpers.tid` (`kind.enum-leaf-items` / `-one`, `kind.ref-leaf-items` / `-one` / `-build` — type-tid threaded through, trailer appended), `doc/reference.tid` (example format fixed), `my-wiki/.../conversation.tid` (format fixed). Multi-card refresh in CP is the remaining gap. No restart needed. |
|v0.1.55 |2026-05-31 |''Unified `default` as a subfilter — dynamic defaults that read from the draft, re-fire after ref/enum changes.'' Replaces v0.1.44's `default` (static literal with `%TODAY%` / `%NOW%` token expansion) with a single subfilter convention identical in shape to `kind.title-formula`. Every default is now a filter expression evaluated against the draft via `[<target-tid>subfilter<default>]`. Authors can express: static literals as `[[planned]]`, current time as `[<now "YYYY0MM0DD0hh0mm0ss0XXX">]`, computed values that read from the draft as `[get[parent]get[caption]]`, and composites that chain through other fields. ''Re-firing on ref/enum changes.'' The existing one-shot apply-defaults at type-pill click can't materialise defaults that depend on other fields (e.g. caption needs parent to be set). `field-input.tid`'s ref-pick / ref-remove / ref-clear / enum-toggle / enum-select action chains now each trail a `<$transclude $variable="kind.apply-defaults-to" …/>` — re-walks the field list, only fills blanks (so user-typed values stick), idempotent. The blank-gate is `!is[blank]` on the COMPUTED value rather than `!has` on the field: formulas that yield empty (because their dependencies aren't set yet) skip the write, leaving the field genuinely empty so the next re-fire can fill it. Text-field edits go through `<$edit-text>` and don't fire actions, so text-field dependencies in formulas don't auto-trigger — declare fields in dependency order (deps first) so the cascade resolves on ref/enum changes. ''Engine.'' New `kind.compute-default(type-tid, field-key, target-tid)` evaluates the field's `default` as `:map[<target-tid>subfilter<currentTiddler>] +[first[]]`. `kind.apply-defaults-to` and `kind.force-apply-defaults` now route through it — both shed the `<$let _today=… _nowts=…>` token-expansion frame; static literals reach them as `[[X]]` filter form, current time via `[<<now "…">>]`. The blank-gate change (`!is[blank]` on computed-value instead of `!has` on field) means partial-computed values skip the write rather than locking the field at empty. ''Type-builder.'' `kind.cell-default` collapses to a single `<$edit-text tag="textarea" class="kind-default-textarea">` for all defaultable typed values (was: enum-single → `<$select>`, number → number input, else → text input with `%TODAY% / %NOW%` placeholder). The unified textarea accepts filter syntax; placeholder + tooltip describe the three patterns (`[[literal]]`, `[<<now "...">>]`, `[get[parent]get[caption]]`). New `.kind-default-textarea` CSS sets monospace font + 24em width + 3.2em min-height. Column header tooltip + raw-JSON schema doc updated accordingly. ''Cascade-palette.'' `kind.cascade-field-default-row` simplifies to a single text-input row binding to `<field-idx>,default`; drops `kind.cascade-field-default-row-dispatch` + `kind.cascade-field-card-single` + `kind.cascade-field-default-picker-items` + `kind.cascade-default-clear-row` (the enum-single quick-pick drill that wrote raw values). The picker can't survive the unification without ugly bracket-wrapping gymnastics; the unified text-input is consistent with how `caption` / `icon` are edited. ''Migration.'' Every existing `default` value in `my-wiki/tiddlers/_system/config/rimir/kind/types/` got rewritten from `"X"` → `"[[X]]"` form (the only existing static values were `active`, `planned`, `low` — 10 tiddlers touched). No `%TODAY%` / `%NOW%` instances were found in the wild (they only ever appeared in this plugin's own docs); doc strings updated to the new patterns. Any external wiki shipping a plugin/shadow type with an unmigrated literal `default` will get the literal string treated as a filter — usually a parse error → empty result → field stays unset (safe failure). ''Conversation type wired up.'' `my-wiki/.../types/conversation.tid` is the showcase: new `planned-at` datetime field defaults to current time via `[<now \"YYYY0MM0DD0hh0mm0ss0XXX\">]`; `caption` defaults to a composed string `[get[parent]get[caption]!is[blank]] :map[<currentTiddler>addsuffix[ at ]] :map[<target-tid>get[planned-at]format:date[DD.MM.YYYY HH:mm]addprefix<currentTiddler>]` that yields e.g. ''"1on1 with Lisa at 31.05.2026 17:30"'' once a parent and planned-at are set, and yields nothing when parent isn't set (so the field stays blank for the cascade to fill it on parent-pick). Field order rearranged to parent → planned-at → caption → status → participants so the cascade resolves correctly: type-pill click fills planned-at + status, leaves caption blank; user picks parent → ref-pick trailer fires `kind.apply-defaults-to` → caption formula now sees parent + planned-at and materialises. User can override caption text or planned-at picker at any point; both stick because the blank-gate prevents overwrites. Parent ref-types widened from `["node"]` to `["jour-fixe","node"]` to match the user's "conversation under a jour-fixe" use case. ''Touches:'' `engine.tid` (+1 function, 2 procedures simplified), `field-input.tid` (5 action-chain trailers added — enum-multi toggle, enum-single select via `actions=` attr, ref-multi remove, ref-single clear, ref-multi/single set), `type-builder.tid` (kind.cell-default collapsed, column header tooltip + schema doc updated), `palette/cascade-helpers.tid` (default-row collapsed; 4 helpers removed), `styles.tid` (+1 CSS rule for `.kind-default-textarea`), `doc/reference.tid` (added `default` to field-def schema table; updated `kind.apply-defaults-to` / `kind.force-apply-defaults` / new `kind.compute-default` entries), 10 type tiddlers in `my-wiki/` (literal defaults migrated to `[[…]]` form), `my-wiki/.../conversation.tid` (planned-at field added, caption formula added, field order rearranged). No JS, no restart. |
|v0.1.54 |2026-05-31 |''Cascade-palette: structured CRUD drill for `kind.auto-children` — no more JSON typing.'' v0.1.53 shipped auto-children with a generic text-input row in CP (and a textarea in Type-builder) for editing the JSON. User feedback: "selecting auto-children in CP just lets me type in text… i would expect more UI/UX support, especially in CP that should be easily possible via drill". This release replaces the text-input row with a multi-stage drill mirroring the existing //kind.fields// editing pattern. ''Drill structure:'' (Stage 1) //Manage kinds → <kind> → ''auto-children (N)''// — outer drill row with reactive entry-count in the caption. (Stage 2) ''Auto-children'' list — one row per existing entry (e.g. ''Streams note — caption: Conversation Minutes'') plus ''+ Add auto-child entry…'' picker. DEL on an entry row removes it with a confirm step. (Stage 3) Per-entry drill — one text-input row per field-override (DEL removes the override) plus ''+ Add field override…'' picker filtered to fields-of-the-child-kind not yet overridden. Text-input rows bind directly to `kind.auto-children` at JSON path `<ac-idx>,fields,<field-key>` via the existing `ca-bind-tiddler` / `ca-bind-field` / `ca-bind-path` protocol — typing into the row mutates the JSON in place. ''Picker filtering:'' the //+ Add auto-child entry…// drill lists all kinds except self (any kind is valid as an auto-child); the //+ Add field override…// drill lists `kind.field-keys` of the child kind minus fields already overridden (so you can't accidentally double-override). ''Orphan handling:'' if an entry references a kind type-key that no longer exists in the wiki, the row renders as ''⚠ <type-key> (kind not found)'' (a leaf, not a drill) with DEL to remove. ''Reactive captions:'' entry rows show ''<kind-caption> — <field-summary>'' where field-summary is "key: value, key: value" joined or "(no field overrides)". The outer drill row's caption reads ''auto-children (N)'' with N derived from the live `jsonindexes[]count[]`. Both update automatically on edit (cp re-evaluates items-from on tiddler change). ''Implementation:'' 4 new procedures in `palette/cascade-helpers.tid`: `kind.cascade-add-auto-child(target-tid, kind-key)` (initialises field to `[]` if unset, appends `{"kind":"<key>","fields":{}}` at next idx), `kind.cascade-delete-auto-child(target-tid, ac-idx)` (rebuilds the array without the entry — same filter-rebuild pattern as `kind.rebuilt-fields-without` to dodge the //jsonset array-deletion converts to object// gotcha), `kind.cascade-set-auto-child-field(target-tid, ac-idx, field-key, value)` (jsonset at path `[ac-idx,fields,field-key]`), `kind.cascade-remove-auto-child-field(target-tid, ac-idx, field-key)` (jsondelete at same path). Plus 17 new row-builder functions chaining through the drill stages (`kind.cascade-auto-children-drill-row` → `-items` → `-entry-row` → `-entry-row-2..5` → `-entry-row-build` / `-entry-row-orphan` / `-entry-items` / `-field-rows` / `-field-row-build` / `-add-field-row` / `-add-field-row-2` / `-add-field-row-build` / `-add-field-items` / `-add-field-leaf-build` / `-children-add-row` / `-children-add-items` / `-children-add-leaf` / `-children-add-leaf-2..3` / `-children-add-leaf-build`). One layout helper `kind.cascade-auto-child-fields-summary(kind-tid, ac-idx)` + `kind.cascade-auto-child-field-summary-pair` to render the "key: value, key: value" summary in entry rows. ''Touches:'' `palette/cascade-helpers.tid` (cascade-kind-edit-items swaps the auto-children meta-row for the new drill-row + ~20 new function/procedure definitions appended), `doc/reference.tid` + `doc/examples.tid` (mention the new CP UX). Type-builder unchanged — text-area edit retained per user's "for creator textfield is ok" earlier preference; CP drill is the primary editing surface. No CSS, no JS, no schema change. |
|v0.1.53 |2026-05-31 |''Three coupled features: surface child kinds on the parent's editing UI, type-safe parent-kinds picker in cascade-palette, and auto-create child instances when a parent is saved.'' ''(1) Child-kinds discoverability from the parent side.'' Type-builder gets a new ''Child kinds'' section listing every kind that declares this type in its `kind.parent-kinds` (links + icon + caption). Cascade-palette //Manage kinds// drill gets one drill-row per child kind under a ''child kinds'' group — drilling in opens the child's own schema-editing surface (same as if you'd picked it from the //Manage kinds// root). New row-builder family: `kind.cascade-child-kind-rows` → `-row` → `-row-2` → `-row-build`. Uses the existing `kind.child-kinds-of` helper (engine.tid) — no new engine functions. The relationship is now visible from BOTH sides: child kinds still declare their parents via `kind.parent-kinds`, but parents can see/navigate to their children without grepping. ''(2) Type-safe parent-kinds picker in CP.'' Replaced the generic text meta-row for `kind.parent-kinds` with a drill-row (`kind.cascade-parent-kinds-drill-row`) that opens a toggle picker (`kind.cascade-parent-kinds-picker-items` + `-toggle-row` + `-toggle-with-key` + `-toggle-build`) listing every kind except self. Each toggle binds to `kind.parent-kinds` as `application/x-string-array` with `ca-true-value` set to the candidate kind's `kind.type` — mirrors the existing ref-types picker pattern (`kind.cascade-field-reftypes-picker-items`). Prevents typos / nonexistent type-keys in `kind.parent-kinds`. Type-builder retains its plain text input (per user's "for creator textfield is ok"). ''(3) Auto-create child kinds on parent save.'' New optional schema field `kind.auto-children` — JSON array, each entry `{"kind":"<child-type-key>","fields":{"<field>":"<value>",...}}`. New procedure `kind.apply-auto-children(parent-tid, type-tid)` walks the array and materialises each child via `$action-createtiddler` with `parent` pre-set to the new parent's title + per-entry `fields` overrides + the child kind's own field defaults applied (via the shared `kind.apply-defaults-to`). The child's `kind.title-formula` evaluates against the seeded draft so it can reference the back-ref. Wired into all 4 create paths: `creator.tid` button (in-tiddler //Creator//), `kind.cascade-save-instance` (CP //+ New <kind>//, both Enter and Ctrl-Enter branches), `kind.cascade-spawn-save` (ref-field //+ Create new <kind>//), and `kind.cascade-create-here` (per-instance //Create here…//). Each path now uses `$savetitle` to capture the post-uniquification parent title (which is then read via textref by the `apply-auto-children` transclude) — was already in place for cascade-save / cascade-spawn / mass-create, added to creator.tid and cascade-create-here. NOT recursive: a child's own `kind.auto-children` does NOT fire automatically (the inner `$action-createtiddler` bypasses the parent save-path that calls this procedure) — keeps shared state (`$:/state/rimir/kind/__last-saved-instance` etc.) simple. New engine helpers: `kind.auto-children-array`, `kind.auto-children-indexes`, `kind.auto-child-kind-at`, `kind.auto-child-fields-at`, `kind.auto-child-field-value-at`, `kind.has-auto-children`. New CP meta-row in `kind.cascade-kind-edit-items` for editing `kind.auto-children` (plain text-input — JSON editor UI would be useful future work). ''Example use case'': set `kind.auto-children: [{"kind":"streams-note","fields":{"caption":"Conversation Minutes"}}]` on a `conversation` kind — every new conversation auto-spawns a `Conversation Minutes` streams-note as a child. ''Touches:'' `engine.tid` (6 new helpers + 1 new procedure), `cascade-helpers.tid` (4 wire-ins to the save paths), `type-builder.tid` (Child-kinds section + auto-children textarea row in metadata table), `palette/cascade-helpers.tid` (4 new row-builder families + drill-row + picker + auto-children meta-row + updated `kind.cascade-kind-edit-items`), `creator.tid` (button captures save title + transcludes auto-children procedure), `doc/overview.tid` + `doc/reference.tid` + `doc/examples.tid` (documentation). No CSS, no JS, no schema migration. |
|v0.1.52 |2026-05-31 |''Add child kinds + cascade-palette "Create here…" action.'' Two coupled features in one wave. ''(1) Child kinds.'' New optional field `kind.parent-kinds` on type-definition tiddlers: space-separated list of parent kind.type keys. Non-empty = child kind. Top-level surfaces filter these out: the in-tiddler creator's primary type-picker (`creator.tid`) now uses `kind.top-level-types` instead of `kind.types-all`, and the cascade-palette ''Create entity'' drill (`kind.create-entity-items`) gains `:filter[<currentTiddler>get[kind.parent-kinds]is[blank]]`. For discoverability, the creator's main pill row is followed by a dimmed second row labeled "Child kinds:" listing all child kinds with a tooltip explaining "Create from within a parent of type: <parents>. Open a parent instance and use the cascade-palette \"Create here…\" action." Find / Manage / Validator surfaces still show ALL kinds — restriction is on the *create* path only. ''(2) Per-instance "Create here…" cascade action.'' New action tiddler `actions/create-here.tid` (`ca-entity-type: kind-entity` + `ca-applies: [<currentTiddler>has[kind.type]] :filter[function[kind.has-create-here-options],<currentTiddler>]` so it appears only when the host has eligible creation targets). Drilling it emits two row clusters via `ca-group`: ''Create child'' (one row per child kind whose `kind.parent-kinds` includes the host's `kind.type`; back-ref field is the standard `parent`) and ''Create reference'' (one row per (kind, field) pair where the kind has a ref-typed field whose `ref-types` includes the host's `kind.type` — field caption baked into the row name as "(as <field-caption>)" to disambiguate when a kind has multiple ref-back paths). Each row drills into a spawn-create form (Save row + Clone-from-existing + per-field edit rows) parallel to the existing `+ Create new <ref-kind>` flow, but with INVERTED link direction: the host's title is pre-set on the NEW instance's back-ref field before save (vs today's `kind.cascade-spawn-save` which writes the new title onto the host's ref field). The pre-set happens both on drill-open (so `kind.eval-title`'s Save-row preview includes it) and at save-time (idempotent, before the `$action-createtiddler $template=draft` copies fields). ''(3) Engine helpers'' added to `engine.tid` (all single-line per [[tw-gotchas-parser-pragma#function single-line]]): `kind.is-child-kind`, `kind.parent-kinds-of`, `kind.parent-kinds-include`, `kind.top-level-types`, `kind.child-kinds-of`, `kind.has-ref-field-to`, `kind.ref-back-fields-of`, `kind.kinds-with-back-ref-to`, `kind.create-here-target-kinds`, `kind.has-create-here-options`, plus `kind.parent-rel-valid` + `kind.viol-parent-kind` for the validator. `kind.has-ref-field-to` and `kind.ref-back-fields-of` use the multi-arg JSON access form (`<type-tid>get[kind.fields]jsonget<currentTiddler>,[typed]match[ref]`) to dodge the `:map` empty-iteration-pushes-empty-string trap that bit v0.1.51 (see [[tw-gotchas-filters#jsonget chained inside :map]]). ''(4) Spawn machinery'' — new procedure `kind.cascade-create-here(host-tid, target-field, target-card, kind-tid)` mirrors `kind.cascade-spawn-save` (`cascade-helpers.tid:108-121`) but inverts the listops direction: writes `host-tid` onto the NEW draft's `target-field`, then `$action-createtiddler $template=draft` carries the back-ref through. Multi-card uses `+[append<host-tid>]`; single-card uses `$action-setfield $value=<<host-tid>>`. A parallel `kind.cascade-create-here-init` procedure runs at drill-open (without the createtiddler step) to prime the draft. New chain `kind.cascade-create-here-fields` parallels `kind.cascade-spawn-fields` with its own save dispatcher pipeline (`kind.create-here-save-or-warn-leaf` → `-for-draft` → `-or-invalid` → `-or-invalid-with-key` → `-or-collision` → `-save-leaf-json`). The intermediate save-or-X functions structurally mirror the spawn family; the leaf-json builder is the only true clone-with-difference (it wires `ca-actions` to `kind.cascade-create-here` instead of `kind.cascade-spawn-save`). The Clone-from-existing row and per-field edit rows are shared via `kind.spawn-clone-row` / `kind.spawn-field-edit-items` after `kind.create-here-field-edit-items` resolves the create-here-prefixed draft tid. Draft tids use a separate prefix `$:/state/rimir/kind/create-here-draft/` (vs spawn's `$:/state/rimir/kind/cascade-spawn-draft/`) so drafts of the two flows on the same host can coexist. ''(5) Cascade-palette Manage-kinds drill'' (palette/cascade-helpers.tid) gets a `parent-kinds` text-edit row between `namespaces` and `title-formula` via `kind.cascade-meta-row,…,[kind.parent-kinds],[parent-kinds],[👪],[525]`. ''(6) Type-builder'' (`type-builder.tid`) gets a matching editor row between `namespaces` and `title-formula` with hint "non-empty = child kind, only creatable from within a parent instance via the cascade-palette ''Create here…'' action". ''(7) Validator'' (`validator.tid`) adds a new check via `kind.viol-parent-kind(type-tid, target-tid)` — fires when the instance's type is a child kind AND the instance's `parent` field is missing OR points to a tiddler whose `kind.type` isn't in the type's `kind.parent-kinds` list. Surfaces a row with detail showing expected parent-kinds joined by " or " plus the current parent's `kind.type` (or `(none)` when no parent set). Instances created via the new spawn flow are validator-clean by construction; hand-edited instances or migrated data get flagged. ''Decisions:'' (a) field is `kind.parent-kinds`; UI uses term ''child kind''. (b) Show-dimmed for child kinds in creator pill row (discoverability); cascade `Create entity` drill excludes them entirely. (c) Multi-parent supported via space-sep list. (d) Ref-back rows are per (kind, field) — no "pick the default" magic when a kind has multiple ref-back paths to the same host type. (e) `Create child` vs `Create reference` cluster separation via `ca-group` — cascade-palette auto-suppresses headers when only one cluster is present. (f) No runtime block on `$action-createtiddler` for child kinds outside the spawn flow — the validator backstop is post-hoc, consistent with every other constraint. (g) `parent` is the standard back-ref field for child kinds — no new convention; ref-back kinds use whichever field they already declare. ''Touches:'' `engine.tid` (12 new functions), `cascade-helpers.tid` (1-line narrow on `kind.create-entity-items` + ~20 new functions and 2 procedures for the create-here machinery), `creator.tid` (top-level filter + dimmed child-kinds row), `type-builder.tid` (1 new editor row), `validator.tid` (1 new violation row), `palette/cascade-helpers.tid` (1 new meta-row entry), `actions/create-here.tid` (new). No CSS, no JS, no schema migration, no breaking changes to existing wikis. No restart required. |
|v0.1.51 |2026-05-29 |''Fix: ref field with no `ref-types` now lists all kind-instances instead of every tiddler in the wiki.'' Two coupled bugs. ''(1) `kind.ref-types` was returning one empty string'' whenever the field had no `ref-types` JSON property (the common "any kind" case the type-builder already advertised via `(any kind)`). Root cause is a TW core quirk in `:map:flat` — when the subfilter returns empty for a given iteration item, `core/modules/filterrunprefixes/map.js:32-34` falls through to `results.push(filtered[0]||"")`, pushing a literal empty string instead of pushing nothing. `kind.ref-types`'s outer `:map:flat[function[kind.field-array-flat],…,[ref-types]]` iterates over the one field-index, the inner `kind.field-array-flat` returns empty when the `ref-types` JSON path doesn't exist, and the empty-string fallback kicks in. The empty string then feeds into `kind.ref-candidates`'s `kind.type<currentTiddler>` subfilter as `kind.type[]` — TW's field operator (`core/modules/filters/field.js:62`) treats a missing field's value as `""`, so `tiddler.getFieldString("kind.type") === ""` matches ''every tiddler that exists in the source''. With `all[shadows+tiddlers]` as the source, the dropdown filled with the entire wiki (minus type-definitions, since `!has[kind.fields]` still filtered those out). Fixed with `+[!is[blank]]` appended to `kind.ref-types` — strips the spurious empty so callers see a genuinely-empty list when ref-types is unset. ''(2) `kind.ref-candidates` now honours the type-builder's documented `(any kind)` semantics.'' Previously, an empty `kind.ref-types` produced no candidates AT ALL (the `:map:flat` over an empty list short-circuits) — so even with the (1) fix, the picker would have rendered "no matches" instead of the intended "any kind-instance is a valid target". Split into three: new helper `kind.ref-candidates-typed(type-tid, field-key)` for the original "instances of each configured ref-type" path (kept structurally identical to the old body), new helper `kind.ref-candidates-any(type-tid, field-key)` for the fallback — `[function[kind.ref-types],…count[]match[0]] :map:flat[all[shadows+tiddlers]has[kind.type]!has[kind.fields]]` fires only when ref-types is genuinely empty, mapping the synthetic "0" sentinel to all kind-instances in the wiki. Combined `kind.ref-candidates` unions both helpers + `+[unique[]]`. Two runs (vs. a `~` else-fallback) so the "ref-types set but no instances exist yet" case stays correctly empty — `~` would have over-triggered there. ''Why split instead of inline:'' the two branches are independent and want distinct sources; `:map:flat` operating on the accumulator makes inline composition fragile (re-mapping accumulator items into a flat-map subfilter would be wrong). ''Verified by CLI render'' against the user's `task` type tid (`kind.fields: [{"key":"parent","typed":"ref","cardinality":"single"}]` — no ref-types property at all): pre-fix, `kind.ref-candidates COUNT=2458` (entire wiki + shadows); post-fix, `COUNT=N` where N = number of kind-instances in the wiki. A parallel `task-limited` type with `ref-types:["task"]` correctly returns ONLY task-typed instances. ''Doc updates:'' `doc/reference.tid` — `ref-types` row downgraded from "Required for ref" to "Optional for ref" with the new "empty = any kind-instance" semantics spelled out; the `ref` typed-values row updated to "`ref-types` optional"; the engine-function row for `kind.ref-candidates` documents the fallback. ''Side note — same TW gotcha is latent in `kind.constraints` and `kind.options`'' (same `:map:flat[function[kind.field-array-flat],…]` shape, both producing spurious empty strings when their respective JSON properties are absent), but their empty values don't leak into UI-breaking behaviour (constraints only ever feed `match[<name>]` / `prefix[<prefix>]` filters that don't match "", and `kind.options` only renders as visible empty `<option>` / pill rows on misconfigured enum fields). Left untouched per "fix-only, no surrounding cleanup" — ping if a parity guard is wanted. ''Touches:'' `engine.tid` (one `+[!is[blank]]` on `kind.ref-types`; `kind.ref-candidates` split into 3 functions), `doc/reference.tid` (3 row updates). No JS, no restart, no version bump in dependents. |
|v0.1.50 |2026-05-28 |''Bridge to cascade-palette ≥ 0.0.79: kind plugin now makes catalogue actions surface in every view automatically.'' Ships a single new config tiddler — `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/entity-type-field` with value `kind.type`. ''What it does:'' cascade-palette 0.0.79 added a configured-field auto-derive path to action discovery — when this config is set, an action's `ca-entity-type: <X>` ALSO matches any row whose tiddler carries `<configured-field>: <X>`. With `kind.type` as the configured field, every catalogue action (orga-palette / domain-palettes / user-authored) now surfaces on Space in any view — Entries, All tiddlers, By namespace, By parent, Hybrid, By date, anywhere a tiddler has `kind.type: <X>`. Zero per-action changes needed in catalogue plugins. ''Why kind owns the bridge:'' `kind.type` is the universal type field across every kind-instance in the wiki — set on type-definition tiddlers themselves AND stamped onto every new draft / saved instance by `kind.apply-defaults-to` / `kind.force-apply-defaults` / save-leaves since v0.1.48. The kind plugin is the natural home for the convention; cascade-palette stays generic (engine reads the config; no field name baked in). ''Caveat:'' configured-field discovery uses an exact field-value compare; rows whose `kind.type` differs from the action's `ca-entity-type` are unaffected. Globals (`ca-entity-type: *`) and explicit per-action `ca-applies` filters still work as before for cross-cutting actions. ''Uninstall path:'' delete the config tiddler (or set its text to empty) → auto-derive disabled → actions surface only through their declared discovery paths. ''(2) Add `ca-applies: [<currentTiddler>has[kind.type]]` to the four instance-actions'' (`open`, `delete`, `edit-fields`, `edit-kind-schema`). These actions already carried `ca-entity-type: kind-entity` — which routed them correctly through the ''Find entity'' catalogue drill (entity-type matched the drill stage's `entityType`). But on a kind-INSTANCE row in tree views (''All tiddlers'', ''By namespace'', etc.), the row's tiddler has `kind.type: <X>`, not `kind.type: kind-entity` — so the bridge config (which is an exact field-value compare) couldn't surface them. The new `ca-applies` filter is a separate discovery path: it matches any row whose tiddler has ANY `kind.type` value. So now SPACE on any kind-instance row (in any view, regardless of its kind.type) opens the action menu with Open / Edit fields / Edit kind schema / Delete. Catalogue path (`ca-entity-type: kind-entity` matching the Find-entity drill stage) is preserved — the two paths union (deduplicated by action title), so the action appears exactly once in each surface. ''Touches:'' `config-cascade-palette-entity-type-field.tid` (new), 4 action tiddlers (+1 field each). Pure tiddler shadows — no restart required (cascade-palette reads the config + ca-applies on every action-load). |
|v0.1.49 |2026-05-28 |''Migrate instance-view preview to cascade-palette's new tag-based side-preview protocol.'' Builds on the v0.1.48 work — same template, same look, different registration mechanism. Requires cascade-palette ≥ 0.0.70. ''(1) Tagged registration.'' `palette/preview/instance-view.tid` now also carries `tags: $:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/side-preview` plus the new tag-fields: `ca-preview-applies: [<currentTiddler>has[kind.type]]`, `ca-preview-name: Instance`, `ca-preview-title: Instance`, `ca-preview-order: 50`. cp auto-attaches this preview to any cascade row whose resolved context has `kind.type` — no per-menu wiring needed. ''(2) Per-menu wirings simplified to opt-in only.'' `kind.kind-find-build`, `kind.kind-create-build-with-draft`, `kind.ref-create-new-row-build-with-draft`, `actions/edit-fields.tid`, `entries/find-entity.tid` no longer declare `ca-preview-template` / `ca-preview-title` — they just opt the stage in to side-preview via `ca-preview-per-row: yes` (browse list) or `ca-preview-context: [[<draft-tid>]]` / `[<parent-picked>]` (create/edit, where the context isn't the row's own title). cp then resolves the candidate list via the tag — currently a single candidate ("Instance"), but any other plugin can ship its own side-preview tagged tiddler and it will appear as an additional pill alongside, navigable with ←/→. ''(3) Side benefit:'' the action-menu sub-drill for a kind-entity (e.g. Find entity → Node1 → action menu) now correctly previews Node1 instead of the action title — cp 0.0.70's inheritance fix locks the inherited context to the drilled-into row, so navigating actions doesn't shift the preview anchor. ''Touches:'' `palette/preview/instance-view.tid` (+ tag + tag-fields), `cascade-helpers.tid` (3 row-build functions trimmed), `actions/edit-fields.tid` (trimmed), `entries/find-entity.tid` (trimmed). Pure tiddler changes — no restart required. |
|v0.1.48 |2026-05-28 |''Move kind-instance view from Ctrl-hold detail drawer into the side-preview pane (+ live preview for create / edit flows + card-style redesign of the view).'' Four changes. ''(1) Move:'' the cascade-palette template `$:/plugins/rimir/kind/templates/kind-entity` (which auto-applied to any tiddler with `kind.type` and rendered the read-only field table inside the Ctrl-hold detail drawer) is gone. Same content now surfaces in the right-column side-preview pane via a per-row registration on the kind-find drill: `kind.kind-find-build` now emits `ca-preview-template: $:/plugins/rimir/kind/palette/preview/instance-view`, `ca-preview-per-row: yes`, `ca-preview-title: Instance`. Drilling "Find by kind → Node" opens the preview pane on the right; ↑/↓ through instances re-resolves the preview's context to the selected row's title → live read-only view follows the cursor. Removes the friction of holding Ctrl to inspect the entity's fields, and reclaims that full-width vertical real-estate below the result list. ''(2) Live preview while creating an instance:'' the "+ New ''<Kind>''" drill (`kind.kind-create-build-with-draft`) now also carries `ca-preview-template` + `ca-preview-context` pointed at the per-kind draft tiddler (`[[$:/state/rimir/kind/cascade-draft/<key>]]`, baked in at row-build time). As the user fills field rows on the left, every edit lands on the draft → cp's side-preview cache invalidates on the draft title's change-hook → the preview re-renders. Same wiring on the ref-create-new spawn drill (`kind.ref-create-new-row-build-with-draft`) so creating a ref'd entity also surfaces the live view of the spawn-draft. ''(3) Live preview while editing an existing instance:'' the ''Edit fields'' action (`actions/edit-fields.tid`) gained `ca-preview-template` + `ca-preview-context: [<parent-picked>]` so drilling Edit fields on any kind-entity opens the preview pane locked to that entity; every field commit re-renders the right pane against the live tiddler. ''(4) View redesign:'' the read-only single-instance view (`$:/plugins/rimir/kind/view`) was rewritten from a plain `<table>` of right-aligned labels to a ''card layout'' — bordered, rounded container with a header band showing a small uppercase ''type chip'' (icon + caption from the kind type-def) and the entity's actual tiddler title (linked, prominent), then a CSS-grid field section with left-aligned label column and value column. Typed-aware value formatting added: ''ref'' values render as clickable pill links (resolved via `kind.resolve-ref`), ''enum'' values as flat pills, ''url'' / ''email'' / ''phone'' as proper anchors with the right href scheme, ''longtext'' preserves whitespace via `pre-wrap`, ''date'' and ''datetime'' format consistently. Computed and blank-valued fields skipped via new `kind.view-field-visible` helper. Empty state when the entity has no non-blank fields says "No values yet — fill fields on the left." instead of rendering an empty table. The header title is now the tiddler's actual title (not the formula-computed title that the earlier draft of the preview template showed at the top in code-formatted form). ''Implementation:'' single new preview template `palette/preview/instance-view.tid` — takes `<<currentTiddler>>` as the entity tiddler (draft or saved), simply transcludes the redesigned view with `target-tid=<<currentTiddler>>`. Falls back to a "not a kind-instance" hint when the tiddler has no `kind.type` (defensive, in case the template inherits into a deeper sub-drill via cp's per-row preview inheritance). New CSS section `=== single-instance view (card layout) ===` in `styles.tid` replaces the four old `.kind-view*` table rules with `.kind-view-card`, `.kind-view-header`, `.kind-view-type-chip`, `.kind-view-title`, `.kind-view-fields` (grid), `.kind-view-row` (display: contents), `.kind-view-label` / `.kind-view-value`, `.kind-view-pills` / `.kind-view-pill`, `.kind-view-link`, `.kind-view-longtext`, `.kind-view-empty`. Light + dark themes via `<<colour …>>` macros, no `!important` (per `[[feedback-no-important]]`). ''(5) Draft stamped with kind.type so the create-flow preview renders.'' Both `kind.apply-defaults-to` and `kind.force-apply-defaults` now `$action-setfield kind.type=…` on the target tiddler in addition to walking field defaults. Reason: the side-preview's instance-view template gates on `[<target-tid>get[kind.type]!is[blank]]` and was falling through to the "Not a kind-instance" message during "+ New ''<Kind>''" because the fresh draft tiddler had only the field defaults written, not the `kind.type` meta-field. Stamping it on draft-build means the live preview renders correctly from the very first drill. Save paths already set `kind.type` explicitly on `$action-createtiddler` so the duplicate is harmless. Reset row also benefits — after the deletetiddler + force-apply chain, the regenerated draft is again a recognisable kind-instance. ''(6) Find-entity preview.'' The ''Find entity'' entry (`entries/find-entity.tid` — generic kind-instance browser, ca-next-scope `[has[kind.type]!has[kind.fields]]`) now also carries `ca-preview-template: $:/plugins/rimir/kind/palette/preview/instance-view` + `ca-preview-per-row: yes`. Every row in that drill is a kind-instance by construction (the scope filter excludes everything else), so navigating ↑/↓ surfaces the same card-style preview that "Find by kind → ''<Kind>''" already showed. ''Touches:'' `palette/preview/instance-view.tid` (new), `templates/kind-entity.tid` (deleted), `view.tid` (rewritten card layout), `engine.tid` (new `kind.view-field-visible` helper + `kind.type` setfield in apply-defaults-to / force-apply-defaults), `styles.tid` (kind-view CSS rewritten), `cascade-helpers.tid` (3 row-build functions extended: `kind.kind-find-build`, `kind.kind-create-build-with-draft`, `kind.ref-create-new-row-build-with-draft`), `actions/edit-fields.tid` + `entries/find-entity.tid` (preview registration). Pure tiddler changes — no re